  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Smart Agriculture Study</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During 2015 and 2016 the South African agricultural sector was seriously affected by drought. Primary production at the level of both the commercial and small holder agriculture was low. Climate adaptation and mitigation technology and sustainable farming technologies can and have to contribute to changed circumstances. The uptake of these technologies in South Africa has to be improved. Through this project technological gaps in South Africa will be identified and further form the basis for facilitating the establishment of Dutch businesses aimed at promoting and transferring climate change mitigation and adaptation skills, knowledge and technologies to assist farmers to improve production and contribute in food security and economic development.</narrative>
  </description>
